Multilevel Adler-Adler analysis. Adler parameters
extracted by making a simultaneous least-squares fit
to capture and fission cross-sections.
For 233U, the analysis goes to 60 eV; for 235U, it
extends up to 100 eV.
Since the adler parameters given are not considered
unique, meaningful standard deviations cannot be
assigned. Uncertainties in values are judged by a
comparison of the experimental cross sections against
the calculated values.
